  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A key requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method for hemolysis QoI confirmation; however, the supporting validation activity was carried out as a numerical-simulation (high-fidelity mesh-refinement study with synthetic boundary conditions). The package narrative argues the simulation results are 'functionally equivalent' to bench experimental data given the controlled inlet/outlet conditions, but the structured activityType field disagrees with the requiredVerificationMethod declared on the bound Requirement, introducing an inference-method mismatch (W-AR-03). Decision: Accepted.",
